create ssh keys:
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "ansible"
copy the public key to the target server:
ssh-copy-id -i /home/ubuntu/.ssh/ansible.pub 192.168.250.30
ssh to the server using the generated keys:
ssh -i /home/ubuntu/.ssh/ansible '192.168.250.30'
first ansible cmd to check connections : 
ansible all --key-file ~/.ssh/ansible -i inventory -m ping
added an ansible.cfg file to avoid using the -i and --key-file options every time:
[defaults]
inventory = inventory
private_key_file = ~/.ssh/ansible
get host informations :
ansible all -m gather_facts
